-: Method Area
+: Stack
-: Heap
-: PC Register

TrueFalseQuestion
The 'String' class in Java is immutable, meaning its value cannot be changed once created.
true

TrueFalseQuestion
A 'static' method can directly access non-static instance variables within the same class.
false

TrueFalseQuestion
The JVM (Java Virtual Machine) is platform-independent, meaning the same JVM executable runs on Windows, Linux, and macOS.
false

Q1Question
The target is a keyword. One of these hints is FALSE:
+: It allows a member to be accessed without creating an instance of the class.
+: It can be applied to variables, methods, and nested classes.
-: A method with this keyword can directly use the 'this' reference.
+: Static variables are shared among all instances of a class.
static

Q1Question
The target is a data type. Identify the false hint:
+: It is a primitive type used to store 32-bit signed integers.
+: The default value for this type when used as an instance variable is 0.
-: It can be used to store decimal values like 3.14 if cast correctly.
+: It has a corresponding wrapper class.
int

Q1Question
The target is a reference type. Which of these hints is FALSE?
+: It is used to achieve total abstraction and multiple inheritance of behavior.
-: A class uses the 'extends' keyword to implement its methods.
+: All variables declared inside it are implicitly public, static, and final.
+: It can contain default and static methods with actual code bodies.
interface

